FOIL is a mechanistic model to study population dynamics under
environmental constraints. 

FOIL is composed of two complementary modules, 
the DEB (Dynamic Energy Budget) to model the bioenergetics 
of anchovy and sardine, 
and the IBM (Individual Based Model) to model the transport 
and movement of individuals as well as the population dynamics. 

Implementation in CROCO by : D.Gourves, M.Caillaud, M.Huret (2024-2026)